-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Mon Mar 24, 2014 06:02AM EDT
-- None



March 24 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 1000 GMT on Monday:

** Nokia <NOK1V.HE> does not expect to close the sale of its phone business to Microsoft <MSFT.O> until April as talks with Asian regulators drag on, it said on Monday, fuelling speculation it may have to make more concessions to get the deal done. [ID:nL5N0ML0XM]  ** Ailing German airline Air Berlin <AB1.DE>, almost 30 percent owned by Abu Dhabi-based Etihad Airways, will be delisted and Etihad will raise its stake to 49.9 percent, a German weekly reported, possibly as a prelude to combining it with Alitalia. [ID:nL6N0MJ05Y]  ** Japanese system integrator NEC Corp <6701.T> said on Monday it would buy A123 Systems' battery systems integration business from China's Wanxiang Group for about $100 million. [ID:nT9N0MD008]  ** AGL Energy Ltd <AGK.AX>, on Monday, took legal steps in hope of getting the go-ahead to pursue a A$1.5 billion ($1.36 billion) acquisition of power supplier Macquarie Generation after its plans were scuttled by Australian competition regulators despite submitting the highest offer. [ID:nL4N0ML1FV]  ** Bahrain's Khaleeji Commercial Bank <KHCB.BH> and unlisted Bank Al Khair have dropped their plan to merge after failing to agree on terms, Khaleeji said in a bourse statement on Monday. [ID:nL5N0ML0TJ]  ** British life insurance and pensions group Standard Life <SL.L> has announced it is in "exclusive and advanced" talks to buy rival Phoenix Group Holdings' <PHNX.L> Ignis Asset Management. [ID:nL4N0MK07W]  ** Hutchison Whampoa <0013.HK> shares fell on Monday after a $5.7 billion deal to sell a stake in its health and beauty retailer to Singapore state investor Temasek Holdings [TEM.UL] disappointed investors hoping for a higher valuation. [ID:nL4N0ML0NS]  ** China's Yanzhou Coal Mining Company Ltd <600188.SS> has decided to walk away from a privatization offer to buy the 22 percent of Yancoal Australia Ltd <YAL.AX> it does not already own, Yancoal said in a statement on Monday. [ID:nL4N0ML0SZ]  ** S-Oil <010950.KS> said on Monday it halted talks to acquire a stake in Australia's United Petroleum after failing to reach an agreement with the petrol and convenience store retailer. [ID:nL4N0ML1MA]  ** Private equity firms Advent International and Bain Capital, along with Danish pension fund ATP, agreed on Monday to buy payment services company Nets Holding from a group of Nordic banks for 17 billion Danish crowns ($3.14 billion), Nets said in a statement. [ID:nL5N0ML1BJ]  ** L'Oreal <OREP.PA> said on Monday it had signed the share purchase agreement selling to Nestle <NESN.VX> its holding in dermatology joint venture Galderma, a key step to completing its deal to buy back shares from the Swiss food giant. [ID:nWEB00KMF]  ** State-run oil group China Petroleum and Chemical Corp (Sinopec Corp) <0386.HK> <600028.SS> said on Monday it aims to complete the sale of up to 30 percent of its marketing business in the third quarter of this year. [ID:nH9N0ME00X]  ($1 = 5.4365 Danish Crowns)